            "candidate": 92,
            "answer_feedback": "Reagan's old lackey in the State Department has made a monumental rise to the Democratic Nomination, and you can't wait to kick at his limping campaign's heels as you race to the finish line. He's only here because he stole the nomination from a dead man, yet his candidacy seems even more lifeless."
