    },
    {
        "model": "campaign_trail.answer_feedback",
        "pk": 12901,
        "fields": {
            "answer": 12898,
            "candidate": 92,
            "answer_feedback": "Given your record, invoking King's name is very, very bold and earns you denouncement from Black leaders across the South. This is not to say that this isn't working, quite the opposite, in fact. You and Nixon laugh about having to face Wallace once more. The mood around the White House is much brighter, nowadays. The assurance of victory will do that."
